<subSubSection id="E6EAC3519605412AC42FF4A2762EAED5" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="0C4D865FC43CF4EC83AFE574CC7DA483" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="81B2FE01ECDD67AA9A0693A7D510DF5D" LSID="9FEA903D-A606-525A-8DEA-6622661BCBF7" authority="Hering, 1931" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Euphlyctina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euphlyctina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Euphlyctina Hering, 1931</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EEEF644940EB1AFDA3126603E8ADDD67" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="D4043AB003A11DB3C45A081109152825" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicName id="1A27B92AFBB2C26577FFE673782F2D1D" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Euphlyctina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euphlyctina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Euphlyctina</taxonomicName>
Hering, 1931, in Seitz, Gross-Schmett. Erde 10: 671 (key), 704. Type species (original designation): 
<taxonomicName id="E7B26BF6E2273C83A5AB28330714E2FB" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Araeogyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Araeogyia phaeopasta" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phaeopasta">Araeogyia phaeopasta</taxonomicName>
Hampson, 1906. Type locality India: Darjeeling.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1F9E724CF8441EFE84DD46152C5245DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="F77DC36539327E3D33D80A9A57D5CBD9" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7FD659AC1996696B0127F022D853C5F9" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicName id="0B70A67C61C8E47673B8C157CBD18412" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Euphlyctina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euphlyctina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3501BDC26343ABA4BA248EA2C60A5F77" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Euphlyctina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a small genus in the family 
<taxonomicName id="23C555E68E6EB5F8ECFF05BF9A2F02AF" authorityName="Duponchel" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Limacodidae</taxonomicName>
, with only two known species: 
<taxonomicName id="92BC0F6ED4E21FFDE861ED080601E851" genus="E." lsidName="E. phaeopasta" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="phaeopasta">
<emphasis id="986B5755E54FE59909396266AD8DC681" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">E. phaeopasta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hampson, 1906) and 
<taxonomicName id="60A35995D846B2983579AD6C093615E2" genus="E." lsidName="E. butvilai" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="butvilai">
<emphasis id="46B457D9FC41EE00B60F9BDD8351B7CA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">E. butvilai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Solovyev &amp; Saldaitis, 2021. The type species 
<taxonomicName id="E33A4210DF5B5D20BCA2F5767CFDC27B" genus="E." lsidName="E. phaeopasta" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="phaeopasta">
<emphasis id="5029EEB9E3EE903FD7D9DFA0E29307E7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">E. phaeopasta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was transferred from the genus 
<taxonomicName id="A65AE2C788C9E5291F465B0AAEE8C8F5" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1893" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Araeogyia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Araeogyia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="87FE9A50AB004B74B0E0687577012057" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Araeogyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hampson, 1893 by 
<bibRefCitation id="CC00288639CF71267B3586012C5C8BA7" author="Hering, M" editor="Seitz, A" journalOrPublisher="Alfred Kernen Verlag, Stuttgart" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="665 - 728" refId="B4" refString="Hering, M, 1931. Limacodidae. In: Seitz, A, Ed., Die Gross-Schmetteringe der Erde, 10. Alfred Kernen Verlag, Stuttgart: 665 - 728" title="Limacodidae." volumeTitle="Die Gross-Schmetteringe der Erde, 10." year="1931">Hering (1931)</bibRefCitation>
, and known only from north India; the second species was discovered in Zhejiang and Yunnan provinces of China (
<bibRefCitation id="B3615999DFEC3DCB68DED89CE6173544" author="Hampson, GF" journalOrPublisher="XI. Bombay Natural History Society, Bombay" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" refId="B3" refString="Hampson, GF, 1906. Lepidoptera-Phalaenae. In: Elwes HJ, Hampson G, Durrant JH (Authors) On the Lepidoptera collected by the Officers in the recent Tibet Frontier Commission. Proceedings of the General Meetings for Scientific Business of the Zoological Society of London. Messrs, Longman, Green, and Co., London, 485-496." title="Lepidoptera-Phalaenae. In: Elwes HJ, Hampson G, Durrant JH (Authors) On the Lepidoptera collected by the Officers in the recent Tibet Frontier Commission. Proceedings of the General Meetings for Scientific Business of the Zoological Society of London. Messrs, Longman, Green, and Co., London, 485 - 496." year="1906">Hampson 1906</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="27E6B04D9EC85CFF04D7BF7739E49CAB" author="Hering, M" editor="Seitz, A" journalOrPublisher="Alfred Kernen Verlag, Stuttgart" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="665 - 728" refId="B4" refString="Hering, M, 1931. Limacodidae. In: Seitz, A, Ed., Die Gross-Schmetteringe der Erde, 10. Alfred Kernen Verlag, Stuttgart: 665 - 728" title="Limacodidae." volumeTitle="Die Gross-Schmetteringe der Erde, 10." year="1931">Hering 1931</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="3F1CD1C369DBE61E8EE8F314A8E43C25" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4999.2.1" author="Solovyev, AV" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" pagination="101 - 116" refId="B18" refString="Solovyev, AV, Saldaitis, A, 2021. Five new species of Limacodidae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenoidea) from South-East Asia. Zootaxa 4999 (2): 101 - 116, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4999.2.1" title="Five new species of Limacodidae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenoidea) from South-East Asia." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4999.2.1" volume="4999" year="2021">Solovyev and Saldaitis 2021</bibRefCitation>
). In 2021, both sexes of 
<taxonomicName id="DB1BFA306067E40B96BF2D6FE3AE33AC" genus="E." lsidName="E. phaeopasta" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="phaeopasta">
<emphasis id="F51DEB9F2156FFFA642D9299297E6B6B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">E. phaeopasta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found in southeastern Xizang; a female of the genus is described below for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
